### AnchorzUp API Test Collection
### Base URL Configuration
@baseUrl = https://localhost:52053
@httpBaseUrl = http://localhost:52054

### Variables for testing
@testId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### 1. Create a new short URL
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/shorturl/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originalUrl": "https://www.google.com",
  "expiresAt": "2025-12-31T23:59:59Z"
}

### 2. Create a short URL without expiration
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/shorturl/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originalUrl": "https://github.com"
}

### 3. Create a short URL with invalid URL (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/shorturl/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originalUrl": "not-a-valid-url"
}

### 4. Get all short URLs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/shorturl

### 5. Get a specific short URL by code
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/shorturl/rlYgu7iG

### 6. Get a non-existent short URL (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/shorturl/nonexistent

### 7. Delete a short URL by ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/shorturl/93b05b01-455a-43f9-a7f4-2ccfcd2d5c4d

### 8. Delete a non-existent short URL (should return 500)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/shorturl/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001

### ============================================
### QR CODE ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### 9. Get QR code for a short URL
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/shorturl/qr/{{testShortCode}}

### 10. Get QR code for non-existent short URL (should return 500)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/shorturl/qr/nonexistent

### ============================================
### REDIRECT ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### 11. Redirect to original URL (this will perform a redirect)
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{testShortCode}}

### 12. Redirect to non-existent short URL (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/nonexistent

### ============================================
### HTTP (NON-SSL) ENDPOINTS FOR TESTING
### ============================================

### 13. Create short URL via HTTP
POST {{httpBaseUrl}}/api/shorturl/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originalUrl": "https://www.microsoft.com"
}

### 14. Get all short URLs via HTTP
GET {{httpBaseUrl}}/api/shorturl

### 15. Redirect via HTTP
GET {{httpBaseUrl}}/{{testShortCode}}



